## 1. Large Dataset Download Problem
﻿
### Problem
Running scripts triggered large downloads (10GB+), including:
- train.100
- train.360
- .parquet files
﻿
### Cause
Using:
load_dataset("librispeech_asr", "clean", ...)
downloads full dataset shards instead of only requested samples.
﻿
### Solution
Replaced with streaming mode:
load_dataset(..., streaming=True)
﻿
### Status


## 2. Audio Data Format Error
﻿
### Problem
TypeError: 'AudioDecoder' object is not subscriptable
﻿
### Cause
Code assumed audio format:
audio["bytes"]
﻿
But actual returned type:
AudioDecoder object (from datasets library)
﻿
### Solution
Used:
dataset.cast_column("audio", Audio(decode=False))
﻿
to restore original bytes/path format.
﻿
### Status


## 3. Missing Trained Model Files
﻿
### Problem
Scripts expect:
./wav2vec2-multispeaker-10db
﻿
but directory does not exist.
﻿
### Cause
Project includes training scripts but not saved model checkpoints.
﻿
### Impact
Cannot run:
- test_multispeaker_trained_model.py
- test_trained_clean_baseline.py
